<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871221-0118 </DOCNO><HL> Sanmark-Stardust Inc.</HL><DD> 12/21/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SMK MVSATENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Sanmark-Stardust Inc., an apparel maker, said its Pear Co. unit launched a tender offer for the shares outstanding of Movie Star Inc. it doesn't own for $8 a share, or $2.4 million.    Sanmark-Stardust's unit previously purchased 64.5% of Movie Star's more than 800,000 shares outstanding for $8 each, or $4.3 million. Movie Star makes apparel. The offer expires midnight Jan 19.    In American Stock Exchange composite trading Friday, Sanmark-Stardust was unchanged at $3.50 a share, while Movie Star closed at $7.75 a share, up $1. </TEXT></DOC>